CALIBRATION STATUS — opcodes in megakernel SASS
  ================================================

  !! SASS AUDIT (nvcc 13.1 / sm_100a) — v3: feedback chains replace XOR accum !!
  ptxas aggressively optimizes calibration loops: loop elimination, CSE,
  copy propagation. XOR accumulation (`x ^= constant`) is period-2 — ptxas
  detects identity after even REPS and eliminates entire loops.

  Fix strategy: feedback chains — make accumulator a direct INPUT to the target
  instruction, so the target itself is the loop-carried dependency. No separate
  XOR step needed. Zero LOP3 overhead for F2FP, PRMT, SEL kernels.

  Remaining XOR accum: K22a (LDS) uses `ld.volatile.shared.b32` to prevent LICM,
  then XOR is valid since ptxas can't prove loaded value is loop-invariant.
  K4 (HFMA2), K7a (IADD), K13a (IMAD), K19a (VIADD), K26a (IABS) use self-
  accumulation (`+r` as both input and output) — loop-carried by design.

  All "f" constraints eliminated (nvcc 13.1 never emits .reg .f32).
  All .reg .u32 → .reg .b32 for cvt bf16x2 correctness.

