  Measurement overhead notes:
    - Feedback chains: accumulator feeds directly into target instruction as input operand.
      Target output replaces accumulator. Loop-carried dependency = target instruction latency.
      With 16 independent chains, throughput = 16/latency instructions/cycle, which saturates
      the pipeline if 16/L >= issue_rate. For F2FP (L~4), 16 chains give 4/cycle.
      ZERO LOP3 overhead — no separate XOR step.
    - K21a, K25a: `add.s32` compiles to IMAD on Blackwell. Overhead is 1 IMAD per ISETP/SEL.
      IMAD is on a different pipe from ISETP/SEL, so throughput measurement is valid (ILP).
    - K22a: XOR accum (LOP3) retained because `ld.volatile.shared.b32` prevents LICM.
      8 LOP3 per 16 LDS (half-interleaved). LOP3 on integer pipe, LDS on memory pipe.
    - mov.b32 bitcast in F2FP kernels (K1, K2, K3, K9) compiles to zero MOV in SASS
      (confirmed: register rename, no real instruction emitted).
    - K8 PRMT: now 16 feedback chains with 8 different control words × 2 second sources.
      All 16 unique — ptxas cannot CSE. Previous version had only 8 (CSE'd to 8).
    - K10 HADD2: only 8 after all fix attempts (ptxas constant-offset + accumulator
      merging). Throughput result valid at 8-wide ILP.

